Bug Barrage+ is rare strong, but I don't think it is rare flashy. Also it is the anchor for a major Automaton archetype. Does that archetype deserve to be destroyed? Maybe. But I wouldn't do that unthinkingly.

It just doesn't make a lot of sense to have this and burn out at rare, and burn out feels much more deserving of that rarity. Ship it is just not a very strong card either, it's asking you to put of statuses in your deck, which will make it harder to draw the ship it, and the reward isn't very good for what it's asking either at just +2 (+3) damage per status, especially when you consider how statuses mess with drawing your functions. 

I can think of very few situations where you would want to take this card, the damage isn't even very good until you already have 2 or more statuses in your deck, so drawing it too early in a fight makes it basically a strike. Not only that, but by the time you are likely to see this (act 1 rare card reward from the boss) you are pretty likely to already have taken most of the front-loaded damage you need, so you will almost never take it over the other rares on offer. Even as a reward for putting statuses in your deck, it's totally outclassed by bug barrage and burn out, and bug barrage is much easier to find at common. I feel like this card really doesn't add anything to automatons kit, and should probably be scrapped for something new entirely.

I think it should exist, it feels like status builds are a bit underrepresented. I think it would do best in the common pool, and I think bug barrage doesn't really fit the common pool well. I say we get spicy and move bug barrage to uncommon and bump up an uncommon into a rare. Not sure what yet, lemme look at the card pool though.

and I still think it would be better in the uncommon pool.

I do think there should be one more status card that gives block in some way, although I'm not sure what at the moment. Current <it's a feature> gives temp dex, and <refactor> gives block when exhausting a status with it.
